STEP 1 — Install Requirements
----Install Minikube
sudo snap install kubectl --classic
----Install kubectl
sudo snap install kubectl --classic
----Install Docker
(Required so Minikube can build images)
Install Helm
sudo snap install helm --classic
install Skaffold
sudo snap install skaffold --classic

STEP 2 — Start Minikube
minikube start
Enable ingress:
minikube addons enable ingress
minikube addons enable metrics-server
STEP 3 — Tell Docker to build inside Minikube
eval $(minikube -p minikube docker-env)

This ensures Docker images you build are visible to Kubernetes inside Minikube.

STEP 4 — Build Docker Images

From project root folder:

Build frontend image:
docker build -t frontend ./frontend
Build backend image:
docker build -t backend ./backend

STEP 5 — Add TLS for Ingress
Generate certificate:
openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 3650 -newkey rsa:2048 \
  -keyout app.local.key -out app.local.crt \
  -subj "/CN=app.local/O=app.local"

Create Kubernetes TLS secret:
kubectl create secret tls app-local-tls \
  --cert=app.local.crt --key=app.local.key
  Add host entry:
echo "$(minikube ip) app.local" | sudo tee -a /etc/hosts

STEP 6 — Deploy EVERYTHING using Skaffold

Just run:

skaffold dev